data.event: Soho expanded dramatically during the 19th century with the construction of numerous houses and factories, and immigration from the Commonwealth was centred in these homes during the 1950s and 1960s.

event.title: took place by the local council during the 1960s and 1970s

data.event: Further housebuilding took place by the local council during the 1960s and 1970s.
The 2001 Population Census found that 25,634 people were living in Soho with a population density of 5,369 people per km² compared with 3,649 people per km² for Birmingham.
